00:20:13,140 --> 00:20:14,940
it's a race to be run.

218
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:21,200
The Christian life, by the way, is not just a dash,

219
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,460
it's a marathon.

220
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:28,680
Over the years that I pastored, I saw so many people

221
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:31,840
that would come and I honestly,

222
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:33,840
the first three or four weeks they were there,

223
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:36,840
I thought Dwight L. Moody had come to Heritage

224
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,520
and man, this was great.

225
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:41,980
And then slowly, they faded.

226
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:48,720
I'll say something, I don't want to be a statistic

227
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:50,880
of having started and not finished.

228
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:57,920
I love fast cars, I love cars, I like NASCAR.

229
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:01,400
I like racing, I like that.

230
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:02,240
Forgive me.

231
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,520
One thing I've never understood,

232
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:07,520
I've never understood being excited

233
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:10,160
about the guy that won the poll.

234
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:14,980
So when he was in time trials, he went the fastest

235
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:18,680
and he gets to start the race in first.

236
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:20,560
Now the truth is, most of the time,

237
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:22,980
when you win the poll, you have set your car up

238
00:21:22,980 --> 00:21:25,740
to win the poll but not go the distance.

239
00:21:26,740 --> 00:21:29,660
And most of the time, people that win the poll

240
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:31,060
don't win the race.

241
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:35,700
Now all I'm saying is, is I don't care much

242
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:38,380
about being the fastest on the first lap,

243
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:41,180
I care about being in first place on the last lap.

244
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:45,860
And I think the spirit of believers today ought to be,

245
00:21:45,860 --> 00:21:50,020
I want to start good, I want to start great

246
00:21:50,020 --> 00:21:52,060
but I want to finish strong.

247
00:21:53,060 --> 00:21:58,060
And Paul says, I have run my race, I've finished my course.

248
00:21:58,940 --> 00:22:00,700
I used to jog.

249
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:04,900
I never would call it running but I did jog.

250
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:07,860
And I would run three miles a day, every day.

251
00:22:07,860 --> 00:22:09,500
I did it for 10 or 12 years,

252
00:22:09,500 --> 00:22:11,660
that's why I have knee surgeries now.

253
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:17,620
But I also quit running when two 70-year-old women

254
00:22:17,620 --> 00:22:19,540
power walked past me, all right.

255
00:22:20,540 --> 00:22:24,460
But I remember thinking to myself, at some point,

256
00:22:24,460 --> 00:22:27,660
I ran the same basic three miles every day,

257
00:22:27,660 --> 00:22:31,820
six days a week and I remember thinking to myself,

258
00:22:31,820 --> 00:22:33,580
at some point, this will get easy.

259
00:22:34,580 --> 00:22:36,980
At some point, I'll probably have to go to five miles

260
00:22:36,980 --> 00:22:39,300
because this three miles will get so easy.

261
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,660
And here's my testimony and I mean it,

262
00:22:41,660 --> 00:22:44,580
not on one day did that three miles get easy

263
00:22:44,580 --> 00:22:46,620
over 10 or 12 years.

264
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:49,500
As a matter of fact, most of the time, every day,

265
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:52,460
on the same three miles that I was running,

266
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:54,740
I would have to say to myself, be a man.

267
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:57,860
Put one foot in front of the other,

268
00:22:57,860 --> 00:23:00,100
my lungs are burning, my legs are hurting

269
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:04,660
and I would have to say, be a man, finish, finish, finish.

270
00:23:07,419 --> 00:23:09,700
Paul says, I've finished my course.

271
00:23:11,980 --> 00:23:15,020
And brother, there were times when I was so tired,

272
00:23:15,020 --> 00:23:17,300
Paul would say, I could barely lift my head up,

273
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:18,580
much less my feet.

274
00:23:20,620 --> 00:23:23,120
There were times when friends would forsake me.

275
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:25,980
There were times when I knew I was trying

276
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:29,320
to do the right thing, but people would come against me.

277
00:23:31,300 --> 00:23:33,900
There were times when Satan fought so hard,

278
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:36,340
but he said, I may not have run fast

279
00:23:36,340 --> 00:23:37,779
and I may have had to tell myself,

280
00:23:37,779 --> 00:23:39,419
put one foot in front of the other,

281
00:23:39,419 --> 00:23:41,660
but bless God, I finished.

282
00:23:41,660 --> 00:23:43,380
Can I tell you my goal in life

283
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:45,260
and I hope your goal in life?

284
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:47,260
I'm gonna finish with the Lord.

285
00:23:50,419 --> 00:23:54,059
I do not wanna be that guy who used to go to church.

286
00:23:55,779 --> 00:23:58,440
I don't wanna be the guy who used to read his Bible.

287
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:03,100
I don't wanna be the guy that used to have prayers answered.

288
00:24:04,580 --> 00:24:07,840
I don't wanna be the guy that used to care about lost souls.

289
00:24:09,500 --> 00:24:12,620
I want to finish strong for the Lord.

290
00:24:12,620 --> 00:24:14,980
I wanna be able like Paul to say,

291
00:24:14,980 --> 00:24:18,459
I have finished my course.

292
00:24:19,540 --> 00:24:21,440
Then he said this, a third statement.

293
00:24:22,899 --> 00:24:24,540
He said, I have kept the faith.

294
00:24:27,140 --> 00:24:28,860
Paul had fought and run the race

295
00:24:28,860 --> 00:24:30,899
according to the word and the will of God.

296
00:24:30,899 --> 00:24:33,339
He had strived lawfully.

297
00:24:33,339 --> 00:24:34,739
He loved people.

298
00:24:34,739 --> 00:24:36,260
He exhorted people.

299
00:24:36,260 --> 00:24:39,420
He rebuked when he was necessary, but he was patient.

300
00:24:39,420 --> 00:24:40,820
He was long-suffering.

301
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:41,940
He was meek.

302
00:24:42,260 --> 00:24:43,100
He was humble.

303
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:45,779
He never made himself the big deal.

304
00:24:45,779 --> 00:24:49,339
It was always about the Lord and reaching people.

305
00:24:49,339 --> 00:24:51,700
He was faithful to the word of God,

306
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:54,100
faithful to the testimony of the Lord.

307
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:58,260
He never veered from the course for the sake of expediency.

308
00:24:58,260 --> 00:25:01,020
He kept the faith.

309
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:05,640
When Paul finally grasped that crown,

310
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:11,200
remember that he has spent a lifetime reaching for it.

311
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:16,420
He has battled ever since the Damascus Road.

312
00:25:18,339 --> 00:25:22,760
He has faced enemy after enemy, but refused to quit.

313
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:24,100
He has gone forward.

314
00:25:25,220 --> 00:25:26,820
He has finished his course.

315
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:28,619
He has come to the end,

316
00:25:28,619 --> 00:25:30,899
and he knows he's about to be martyred,

317
00:25:30,899 --> 00:25:33,580
but bless God, he has kept the faith.

318
00:25:33,580 --> 00:25:35,300
He has not recanted.

319
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:39,339
He has not trimmed the message for his entire lifetime.

320
00:25:39,339 --> 00:25:41,500
From the Damascus Road on,

321
00:25:42,020 --> 00:25:45,100
he has said, Jesus, I will suffer with you.

322
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:48,899
Jesus, I want to know your power through the resurrection.

323
00:25:48,899 --> 00:25:51,779
Jesus, I am pressing toward the mark.

324
00:25:51,779 --> 00:25:53,959
I am pressing toward the mark.

325
00:25:53,959 --> 00:25:55,940
I don't care what has gone behind.

326
00:25:55,940 --> 00:25:57,520
I'm following you,

327
00:25:57,520 --> 00:26:01,080
and I'm looking for the day when you appear.

328
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:06,059
I can have that crown.

329
00:26:07,020 --> 00:26:08,839
I have people all the time telling me,

330
00:26:08,839 --> 00:26:12,920
