421
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:04,220
You're not going to say, oh shucks, no, I don't want that.

422
00:30:04,220 --> 00:30:07,900
You're going to be glad.

423
00:30:07,900 --> 00:30:11,180
You're going to receive it gladly.

424
00:30:11,180 --> 00:30:17,260
Third, occupying precedes appearing.

425
00:30:17,260 --> 00:30:22,300
If we're ever going to get to that crown, then we've got to understand that reaching

426
00:30:22,300 --> 00:30:26,220
for it has to be part of our life.

427
00:30:26,220 --> 00:30:30,500
We've got to be focused on that goal just like Paul was.

428
00:30:30,500 --> 00:30:34,220
Whether it takes us through suffering, whether it takes us to the mountaintop of victory,

429
00:30:34,220 --> 00:30:37,900
we've got to be pressing towards that mark.

430
00:30:37,900 --> 00:30:44,140
We've got to be obedient to the plan of life that God has given us.

431
00:30:44,140 --> 00:30:49,420
If you're a secular job and serving in a local church, God created that path for you and

432
00:30:49,420 --> 00:30:53,740
your path is as valuable as pastors are mine.

433
00:30:53,740 --> 00:30:56,160
Our path is as valuable as Paul's.

434
00:30:56,160 --> 00:31:02,240
We may not be called to the shipwreck or to the jailhouse, but our path of obedience

435
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:05,680
is as essential as Paul's was.

436
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:15,200
And then, we've got to occupy our place until Jesus calls for us or until Jesus comes.

